def: Unwonted; unused; unaccustomed. [Archaic] Sir W. Scott.
Any one of several species of nudibranchiate mollusks of thegenus Doris and allied genera, having a smooth, thick, convex yellowbody.
Capable of being congealed; capable of being converted intojelly.
To induce hypnotism in; to place in a state of hypnotism.
Cloth for vests; a vest pattern.
Of or pertaining to a station. [R.]
A crystalline acid substance, CH2N4, which may be regarded aspyrrol in which nitrogen atoms replace three CH groups; also, any ofvarious derivatives of the same.
An order of ganoid fishes, including the sturgeons; -- socalled on account of their cartilaginous skeleton.
The involute of a curve. See Involute, and Evolute.
